ter und öffentlicher Wohltätigkeit sowie zum Nebeneinander von observanten und nicht-observanten Juden. Dieser Teil des Jerusalemer Talmuds hat so gut wie keine Entsprechung im Babylonischen Talmud. Ohne seine Kenntnis bleiben die diesbezüglichen Regeln der jüdischen Tradition unverständlich.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aRabbinical literature. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / General.2bisacsh1 aGuggenheimer, Heinrich W., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Theology and Religious Studies 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023854908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Theology and Religious Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110638165oZDB-23-GTR0 cprintz978311016691040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110816587zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110816587zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110816587/original  a978-3-11-023854-9 DGBA Backlist Theology and Religious Studies 2000-2014 (EN)c2000d2014  a978-3-11-023857-0 DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA  aZDB-23-GTRc2000d2014